</h3><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-dtMgUX gYEGeC pf-47_ pf-heading-1-h3"><strong>Regulation and compliance</strong></h3><p class="sc-cZMNgc hqfPHB pf-49_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">The Law Society of Scotland ensures that all solicitors comply with the Solicitors (Scotland) Act 1980, which outlines the professional standards and ethical conduct required in the legal field. This includes rigorous assessments and audits of legal practices to maintain quality and integrity.































</p><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-dtMgUX gYEGeC pf-51_ pf-heading-1-h3"><strong>Education and training</strong></h3><p class="sc-cZMNgc hqfPHB pf-53_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">Continuous professional development is a cornerstone of the Society's mission. They offer various training programmes and resources to help solicitors stay updated with the latest legal developments, ensuring they provide the best possible service to their clients.































</p><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-dtMgUX gYEGeC pf-55_ pf-heading-1-h3"><strong>Public protection</strong></h3><p class="sc-cZMNgc hqfPHB pf-57_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">By handling complaints and taking disciplinary actions when necessary, the Society protects the public from malpractice and ensures that any breaches of conduct are addressed promptly and fairly.
































